result.execSummary:
The defendant Nicole J Fischer was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Nicole J Fischer is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Nicole J Fischer was found guilty of Possession of Narcotic Drugs, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(am).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Conditions of extended supervision are the same as the conditions of probation.

miscConds.notes: Cash bond shall be applied to costs due with balance being paid as a condition of probation.    If probation is revoked or will discharge with outstanding financial obligations due, a civil judgment shall be entered for the balance due.

Defendant shall not possess/consume any controlled substance without a valid prescription.

Defendant shall not be present in any place where controlled substances are illegally purchased, consumed or sold.

Defendant shall have no direct or indirect contact with Amanda K, Robert S or Jane D.

Defendant shall participate in all counseling and/or treatment programs directed by the probation agent, including AODA assessment/treatment.

Defendant shall provide DNA sample.

Defendant shall maintain absolute sobriety.

Defendant shall submit to random drug screens, including blood, breath or urine.

Defendant shall obtain prior approval of her probation agent before taking any prescription.

Defendant shall notify any medical or healthcare provider of opiate addiction prior to obtaining a prescription.

timeConds.notes: With Huber privileges consistent with the rules of the jail while the inmate maintains a minimum security status. The defendant, at the discretion of the Sheriff, may perform community service work as an inmate worker in the county jail and shall earn statutory good time for same.
